content.description: This highball slab is a fun problem on good knobs and crystals.
content.location: On the uphill, slabby side of the Kingdom boulder, on the far left side.

content.description: It starts behind and tree and goes up the blunt arete of the Northwest face of the Kingdom Boulder
content.location: Northwest face of the Kingdom Boulder and starts behind a tree

content.description: An "S" shaped, moderatly overhung crack over a pit.  You will be hanging from your jams, and they better be solid.     A wonderful apperatus and test of your crackmongering skills. Plus, the falls are clean.
content.protection:
medium sized cams 

  consider having your belayer stand down in the pit.
content.location: On the Southwest corner of the Kingdom boulder, dangling over a 15ft drop off.

content.description: From the start holds of Zilchness, traverse to the right through a delicateÂ sequence on small crimps and crystals. There is a bomber hold in ths middle of the boulder, from there climb up through the crux of Don't Void Your Pants
content.location: On the slabby, northwest face of the Kingdom boulder

content.description: This problem climbs the face to the left of Grodie Crack.  It starts with a hand in a thin left-angling seam and a huge high-step.  At no time does it use the holds on Grodie Crack.
content.location: Kingdom Boulder to the left of Grodie Crack

content.description: Rotten finger crack/flake often used as down-climb for all the routes on the Kingdom boulder.  It is very rotten so do not pull too hard and do not trust anything!
content.protection: Boulder.  Can use gear but not needed. Can set a anchor on the big flack above.
content.location: Eastern face of Kingdom boulder.  The obvious rotten crack.

content.description:
Despite it's obvious and convenient location, this highball boulder problem somehow eluded mention in the guide books. Nevertheless, it's a fun and exciting problem. Just don't fall if you decide to boulder it. 

  A couple face moves put you into a hand crack that otherwise requires a flared and overhanging start. It becomes a lower angle fist crack as you gain height. The crux comes early, it gets easier once you're in the crack.
content.protection: Unfortunately, there is a boulder below this crack that creates a pretty ugly landing hazard. Pads might help. People sometimes rope up for it.
content.location: Located in the trees West of the Kingdom Boulder. It can be found along a well used and obvious foot trail. It is between the parking lot and Solo Boulder.

content.description: Behind and to the left of the big tree.  Route with solid crystals covered but lichen.  Need patience.  As you get higher off the ground some of the crystals gets smaller and more questionable!
content.location: East fast of Kingdom Boulder behind and to the left of the tree.

content.description: On the southeast corner of The Kingdom Boulder you will see a triangular rock leaning against the Kingdom Boulder.  Heel Hook and crimp the downhill arete while you ascend theis odd formation.  A tenuous downclimb is found on the north side of the boulder.
content.location: Enchanted Rock, Kingdom of Zilch, Kingdom Boulder Southeast corner.

content.description: Fun highball slab on good knobs and crystals with a few smears. Crux is up high and committing, so don't fall!
content.location: Just to the left of Scrambled Egg Sandwich, on the uphill, slabby side of the Kingdom Boulder.

content.description: The East end of front side boulders.  Home to many quality boulder problems and an easier access to the rest of the kingdom
